bio.experienceSummary:
Hi, 

My name is LZ and I am scientist here in NJ. I hold a masters degree in statistics and a bachelors in psychology! I have been babysitting for the past 12 years. I speak 3 languages fluently: English, French, and Arabic. I have watched as young as newborns all the way to pre-teens. I have my own car! Please message if interested. 

I'd describe my personality as kind, patient, compassionate.

I started working with kids when 12 years ago! 

In my spare time, I like to babysit, play volleyball with my friends, take long walks in nature, and nap!

I have over 10 years of experience working in childcare with children of all ages. I enjoy doing crafts and outdoor activities! I look forward to hearing from you and answering any questions you may have for me!

bio.experienceSummary:
Good evening my name is Ashley and I currently work full-time as a childcare provider/nanny.
With over 10 years of experience providing childcare to small children, (and support to their families), I skillfully manage details and give care to the most precious among us in this life. More, I am equipped and experienced at handling stressful situations and can adapt easily to changing needs very quickly. 
I am currently seeking an opportunity where I can apply my extensive child care experience in a role where I can utilize my skills of managing details, caring for others, and seeing projects through to completion. I am polished and professional, and present myself as a mature and responsible go-getter. I have been acknowledged for my talent of getting tasks done and getting them done correctly and on time. 
I am available at your convenience for an interview, and look forward to an opportunity to discuss my credentials in greater detail. 

Sincerely,
Ashley

description.originalText: Ashely is an amazing nanny/baby sitter. She worked for us for almost 3 years during pandemic . My kids adored her . She was very flexible and accommodating. I would strongly recommend Ashley.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello Dear family!
My name is Zamira and I am an experienced nanny and babysitter. I live in Carteret and would love to connect with your family to see if we can be a good match.

- I have 4 years of experience with children from ages of 1-15 years old (Me being +18) and many years of experience helping to take care of my little brother and cousins.
- I speak English (Advanced) and Spanish (Native Speaker). 
- Pet friendly
- Good swimmer
- Non smoker
- Fully vaccinated
- CPR certified
- Love cooking and baking
- Arts and crafts enthusiast
- I enjoy expending time with children and being a caregiver for them. I consider myself friendly, loving, patient, reliable, creative, clean, organized and open minded.
- I'll be happy to share with you my references from the families I've worked for.

I absolutely love children. I've worked as a camp counselor, a nanny, and as a teacher at early learning centers. I am a mom and understand the importance of trust and safety when it comes to your child's caregiver. I treat every child I care for as my own and love to introduce them to different experiences, such as music. I've been playing guitar for 20 years and singing for even longer. I also implement the RIE philosophy and Reggio philosophy in my caregiving.

description.displayText:
We've had a number of different nannies for my son (now a little over 2) and Bridget has been by far the most outstanding nanny we've ever had. She is easy to communicate with and extremely professional in how she approaches the job, always punctual if not early, and pitches in so that we can end our work day in a restful home. 

Our son loves her because she patiently reads books to him (even making a good effort on the non-English books!), sings songs, comes up with fun sensory and art activities, and generally treats him respectfully and includes him in all care giving, in line with the RIE philosophy. It really makes a difference in how independent he feels, which benefits all of us.

Our setup was that Bridget would bring her own daughter (4 years old) with her through the summer. The two children had a great time together and if they ever did clash, Bridget always set boundaries fairly and firmly. 

I'm going on maternity leave for a few months but would rehire her in a heartbeat.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello everyone!

I have experience with kids on all ages so i'm able to provide a safe and rich environment and understand their needs depending on the stage they are so you won't have to worry about them while i'm on guard!

I consider myself a very positive, reliable, fun, creative and very patient person who loves being around little ones, plus I follow the idea of gentle parenting style.

Communication is a key for me and i'll keep you posted on how the shift is going and can do extra chores that are need it upon request.

description.originalText: Laura was absolutely fantastic taking care of our 18month old boy. She came right in, listening to everything we had to share about his schedule, and had him laughing and in her arms within minutes. She fed him, played around the house, and bathed him before putting him down for bed. She kept us updated while we were out with cute pictures of him. We would definitely recommend her for any family looking for someone both caring and super reliable.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! My name is Story, and I am a reliable and nurturing caregiver with over 5 years of experience caring for children of all ages. I am passionate about creating safe, fun and engaging environments for kids, whether it's helping with homework, playing games or finding creative ways to be active. I'm also happy to assist with light housekeeping, meal preparation and errands to help make your life a little easier. I am also a pet lover and would be happy to care for them as well. Parents love that I am dependable, responsible, and focused on making every experience positive for their children. I'd love to support your family in any way I can!

I have over 25 years of experience with newborns, infant, toddlers, twins and school-aged children. I describe myself as a loving, responsible and caring person. I like walking to parks, performing daily activities with other children and parents will always be well informed before I make any decisions, so they can always count on me when they need me. I have my First Aid and CPR certification and I am also a certified newborn care specialist. I drive very carefully and I have never had an accident while driving because a child's safety is very important to me. I truly love what I do and I am excited to start a new journey with a new family.

description.originalText: Any family with young children would be so lucky to have Yolanda! She's a career nanny with 20+ years of experience that came highly recommended to us by all of her previous families. She's very caring, loving and energetic and made my transition back to work so much easier. My son would get so excited when she walked through the door in the morning. Yolanda kept my son very active, organized playdates, did laundry, prepared nutritious meals, and kept the house very tidy. She's a newborn care specialist, so is very knowledgeable on milestones. She speaks both Spanish and English, has her own car/transportation, and is CPR and First Aid certified.
